1
00:01:37,340 --> 00:01:37,859
Gross.

2
00:01:38,099 --> 00:01:38,620
Take the dishes out.

3
00:01:41,959 --> 00:01:42,840
Dinner's ready.

4
00:01:43,620 --> 00:01:43,939
Okay.

5
00:01:44,420 --> 00:01:44,840
Come on, Yi.

6
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:46,140
Bo,

7
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:48,180
you looked awfully serious

8
00:01:48,180 --> 00:01:50,079
in those pre-wedding photos.

9
00:01:50,079 --> 00:01:51,159
Don't look.

10
00:01:51,159 --> 00:01:52,659
That's not me.

11
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:54,900
Is the soup ready?

12
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:55,540
Here you go.

13
00:01:55,540 --> 00:01:55,980
Coming.

14
00:01:55,980 --> 00:01:56,859
Gosh, it's super hot.

15
00:01:56,859 --> 00:01:57,219
Here.

16
00:01:57,219 --> 00:01:57,640
Careful.

17
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:59,099
Down it goes.

18
00:01:59,099 --> 00:02:00,260
You two just sit there and watch?

19
00:02:00,260 --> 00:02:00,980
It's burning hot.

20
00:02:00,980 --> 00:02:02,200
Feel it?

21
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:04,599
- Qiao,
- You're such a pain.

22
00:02:04,599 --> 00:02:05,180
beat him.

23
00:02:06,420 --> 00:02:07,760
Don't go easy on him.

24
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,620
You're asking for it.

25
00:02:11,340 --> 00:02:12,580
You're

26
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:13,520
always egging Qiao

27
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,460
how to boss me around.

28
00:02:14,860 --> 00:02:15,500
When are you gonna get a girlfriend

29
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:16,219
to do the same to you?

30
00:02:17,620 --> 00:02:18,379
I...

31
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:19,740
I'll just

32
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:20,419
leave it to fate.

33
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,979
If the right one shows up, I'm in.

34
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:26,460
If not, this is fine too.

35
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:27,879
Makes sense.

36
00:02:28,259 --> 00:02:28,780
Come on.

37
00:02:28,780 --> 00:02:29,139
Help yourselves.

38
00:02:29,139 --> 00:02:30,020
The soup is amazing.

39
00:02:30,020 --> 00:02:30,719
I simmered it all morning.

40
00:02:30,719 --> 00:02:31,139
Try this.

41
00:02:32,020 --> 00:02:32,979
The veggies are good too.

42
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,180
Spill it.

43
00:02:41,439 --> 00:02:43,000
What's going on with you and Miao Jing?

44
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,520
I have

45
00:02:58,500 --> 00:02:59,620
no idea what she's thinking now.

46
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:00,840
That's easy.

47
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:01,659
Here's the trick.

48
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:03,699
When girls say no,

49
00:03:04,539 --> 00:03:05,340
they actually mean yes.

50
00:03:06,099 --> 00:03:07,139
When they say they're fine,

51
00:03:07,939 --> 00:03:08,939
it means they're mad.

52
00:03:09,539 --> 00:03:11,219
Just do the opposite of what they say.

53
00:03:11,419 --> 00:03:12,219
Nonsense.

54
00:03:12,740 --> 00:03:14,060
Absolutely nonsense.

55
00:03:14,060 --> 00:03:15,419
How can you do the opposite?

56
00:03:15,979 --> 00:03:17,139
Just take their word for it.

57
00:03:17,860 --> 00:03:18,819
Are you married?

58
00:03:19,719 --> 00:03:20,319
No.

59
00:03:21,379 --> 00:03:22,379
Then who in this room

60
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:24,680
has the most experience?

61
00:03:26,419 --> 00:03:26,979
You do.

62
00:03:27,659 --> 00:03:28,280
You silly thing.

63
00:03:30,180 --> 00:03:31,000
Take the dishes back.

64
00:03:31,740 --> 00:03:32,460
Kick them out.

65
00:03:34,620 --> 00:03:35,479
Just shut up and eat.

66
00:03:40,580 --> 00:03:41,659
What if

67
00:03:42,379 --> 00:03:43,580
she says "it depends"

68
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:45,300
and tells me to figure it out myself?

69
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,120
That's

70
00:03:50,139 --> 00:03:50,819
tougher.

71
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:52,800
But I think

72
00:03:53,599 --> 00:03:54,280
it depends on

73
00:03:54,620 --> 00:03:55,340
the specific situation.

74
00:03:56,539 --> 00:03:57,539
Maybe try

75
00:03:57,860 --> 00:03:58,860
a different approach?

76
00:03:59,819 --> 00:04:00,500
Like

77
00:04:01,319 --> 00:04:02,560
act cute around her?

78
00:04:03,639 --> 00:04:04,039
Get lost.

79
00:04:04,039 --> 00:04:05,580
Stop giving him bad ideas.

80
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:07,219
You always dodge problems

81
00:04:07,219 --> 00:04:07,699
this exact same way

82
00:04:07,699 --> 00:04:09,219
instead of facing your mistakes.

83
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:10,439
That's why I

84
00:04:10,439 --> 00:04:11,460
wanted to move out before.

85
00:04:22,620 --> 00:04:23,579
Yi,

86
00:04:24,319 --> 00:04:25,100
I think first

87
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:26,579
you need to figure out

88
00:04:26,579 --> 00:04:27,319
what the real problem

89
00:04:27,319 --> 00:04:28,540
is between you two.

90
00:04:29,220 --> 00:04:30,540
Dating and marriage

91
00:04:30,540 --> 00:04:31,500
are two different things.

92
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:32,980
Dating's all about romance.

93
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:34,000
You can overlook

94
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,019
small conflicts

95
00:04:36,060 --> 00:04:36,860
for you don't think too far ahead.

96
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,879
But marriage

97
00:04:38,980 --> 00:04:39,839
is different.

98
00:04:40,459 --> 00:04:41,899
You can't just brush things off.

99
00:04:42,139 --> 00:04:42,899
Exactly.

100
00:04:43,019 --> 00:04:43,819
Listen to her.

101
00:04:43,819 --> 00:04:44,620
She's right.

102
00:04:45,819 --> 00:04:46,920
A relationship

103
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,220
needs equal effort.

104
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:49,300
If one person

105
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:50,139
keeps giving

106
00:04:50,139 --> 00:04:51,620
while the other only takes,

107
00:04:51,759 --> 00:04:53,519
the balance will eventually fall apart.

108
00:04:57,639 --> 00:04:58,160
So

109
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:00,620
what should I do?

110
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,899
I'm just sharing some general ideas.

111
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:04,639
You'll have to

112
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:06,319
figure out the rest yourself.

113
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:09,800
Maybe

114
00:05:10,139 --> 00:05:10,920
start with

115
00:05:11,100 --> 00:05:12,459
small things.

116
00:05:12,759 --> 00:05:13,660
Call her at night

117
00:05:14,139 --> 00:05:16,379
and say things like "I miss you,"

118
00:05:16,839 --> 00:05:17,680
"are you tired?",

119
00:05:18,279 --> 00:05:19,500
and "you've done a good job."

120
00:05:21,379 --> 00:05:21,980
What do you think?

121
00:05:23,279 --> 00:05:24,000
Why are you laughing?

122
00:05:24,579 --> 00:05:25,620
No, no, no.

123
00:05:25,879 --> 00:05:26,740
She has a good point.

124
00:05:26,899 --> 00:05:28,019
You really are a love expert.

125
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:29,060
Let's toast to Qiao.

126
00:05:29,279 --> 00:05:29,839
To Qiao.

127
00:05:29,839 --> 00:05:30,620
To Qiao.

128
00:05:30,699 --> 00:05:31,860
Alright, let's eat.

129
00:05:32,819 --> 00:05:33,459
Are you praising me?

130
00:05:33,660 --> 00:05:34,259
Of course we are.

131
00:05:34,379 --> 00:05:35,339
We really are.

132
00:05:35,459 --> 00:05:35,959
Isn't that nice?

133
00:05:51,319 --> 00:05:52,040
[Start with]

134
00:05:52,259 --> 00:05:53,620
[small things.]

135
00:05:53,959 --> 00:05:54,899
[Call her at night]

136
00:05:55,420 --> 00:05:56,040
[and say things]

137
00:05:56,660 --> 00:05:57,579
[like "I miss you,"]

138
00:05:58,019 --> 00:05:58,860
["are you tired?",]

139
00:05:59,519 --> 00:06:00,839
[and "you've done a good job."]

140
00:06:14,939 --> 00:06:15,379
[Hello?]

141
00:06:15,939 --> 00:06:16,680
Are you off work?

142
00:06:19,339 --> 00:06:20,300
What happened to your voice?

143
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:25,800
Nothing.

144
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,279
Just breathed in some cold air.

145
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,720
Have you eaten?

146
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:39,000
I have a dinner with a client later.

147
00:06:39,459 --> 00:06:40,040
What about you?

148
00:06:40,620 --> 00:06:42,060
[I ate at Bo's place,]

149
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:43,639
[but I didn't eat much.]

150
00:06:44,259 --> 00:06:45,100
I'll head

151
00:06:46,100 --> 00:06:46,779
home soon.

152
00:06:47,579 --> 00:06:48,180
[What?]

153
00:06:48,879 --> 00:06:50,319
You can't eat when I'm not around?

154
00:06:57,019 --> 00:06:58,000
What's so funny?

155
00:07:01,060 --> 00:07:01,740
I miss you.

156
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,000
I miss you too.

157
00:07:11,620 --> 00:07:12,139
Well,

158
00:07:12,459 --> 00:07:13,560
hearing you say that,

159
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:14,699
I've suddenly got an appetite.

160
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:16,120
I'll eat a bit more later.

161
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,019
Go grab something too.

162
00:07:18,639 --> 00:07:19,420
And wait for me,

163
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:20,240
okay?

164
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:25,759
Bye.

165
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:47,600
[Miao Jing Coming Home]

166
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:41,519
Hello?

167
00:09:43,019 --> 00:09:43,559
[Hello? Chen,]

168
00:09:44,059 --> 00:09:44,740
[it's me, Ma Yang.]

169
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:49,559
It's late.

170
00:09:49,559 --> 00:09:50,259
What's going on?

171
00:09:51,059 --> 00:09:52,200
Yu and I are

172
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,080
at the hospital.

173
00:09:53,539 --> 00:09:54,159
Jing's mom

174
00:09:54,159 --> 00:09:55,220
fainted at the hotel just now.

175
00:09:58,460 --> 00:09:59,019
Which hospital?

176
00:09:59,460 --> 00:10:00,120
We're at

177
00:10:00,620 --> 00:10:01,960
Vineton First People's Hospital.

178
00:10:02,179 --> 00:10:03,019
[I'm on my way.]

179
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:15,539
Hello, Yu.

180
00:10:15,779 --> 00:10:16,460
I just called Chen.

181
00:10:16,460 --> 00:10:17,379
He said he'll be here soon.

182
00:10:17,779 --> 00:10:18,019
Right.

183
00:10:18,019 --> 00:10:18,879
I can only wait for him to

184
00:10:18,879 --> 00:10:19,700
come and fill out the forms.

185
00:10:20,059 --> 00:10:20,620
He's on the way.

186
00:10:21,139 --> 00:10:21,759
Alright.

187
00:10:21,919 --> 00:10:22,240
Okay.

188
00:10:23,759 --> 00:10:24,279
Ma Yang.

189
00:10:24,799 --> 00:10:25,179
Chen.

190
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:25,720
Where is Ms. Wei?

191
00:10:26,259 --> 00:10:27,220
She's still in the ER.

192
00:10:27,220 --> 00:10:28,039
She hasn't come out yet.

193
00:10:28,039 --> 00:10:29,000
Yu is with her.

194
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:30,700
How is she now?

195
00:10:30,820 --> 00:10:31,679
How did she suddenly pass out?

196
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,820
I'm not sure either.

197
00:10:33,679 --> 00:10:34,279
All I've got

198
00:10:34,279 --> 00:10:35,279
is her ID card.

199
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:36,860
There's a lot of info I don't know,

200
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,299
so I've been waiting for you.

201
00:10:40,259 --> 00:10:41,139
Sorry to trouble you two.

202
00:10:41,919 --> 00:10:42,419
It's okay.

203
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,519
Have you contacted Miao Jing?

204
00:10:44,139 --> 00:10:44,980
I called her,

205
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:45,779
but she didn't answer.

206
00:10:46,299 --> 00:10:47,100
She's probably busy.

207
00:10:49,039 --> 00:10:49,399
She's been

208
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:50,399
overwhelmed with work these days.

209
00:10:50,980 --> 00:10:51,840
Don't tell her yet.

210
00:10:52,159 --> 00:10:52,919
I'll handle things here.

211
00:10:53,759 --> 00:10:54,159
Okay.

212
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:57,980
Yu.

213
00:10:59,279 --> 00:10:59,879
You're here.

214
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:01,240
How long has she been in there?

215
00:11:02,399 --> 00:11:03,399
Over half an hour.

216
00:11:03,399 --> 00:11:04,440
The doctor still hasn't come out.

217
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,700
Where's Wei Mingzhen's family?

218
00:11:42,159 --> 00:11:43,299
Doctor, how is she?

219
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,279
After emergency treatment,

220
00:11:45,279 --> 00:11:46,580
the patient is out

221
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:47,480
of immediate danger.

222
00:11:48,539 --> 00:11:49,659
But we've found

223
00:11:50,159 --> 00:11:51,220
that the cancer cells

224
00:11:51,220 --> 00:11:52,220
have already spread

225
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:53,179
to her lungs and liver.

226
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:55,080
She's at Stage IV breast cancer.

227
00:11:56,860 --> 00:11:57,679
How could this happen?

228
00:11:59,799 --> 00:12:00,879
How much time does she have left?

229
00:12:01,899 --> 00:12:02,919
That depends on

230
00:12:02,919 --> 00:12:03,700
the treatment plan

231
00:12:03,820 --> 00:12:05,759
and how well she recovers.

232
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,440
If her condition improves,

233
00:12:07,639 --> 00:12:08,539
chemotherapy may be an option.

234
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,860
If not, we can only

235
00:12:10,220 --> 00:12:11,220
focus on conservative treatment.

236
00:12:12,159 --> 00:12:12,860
And

237
00:12:13,419 --> 00:12:14,580
judging by her current condition,

238
00:12:14,580 --> 00:12:16,419
she likely knew about it for a while.

239
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,360
Please be prepared

240
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,399
for the worst.

241
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:20,259
Okay.

242
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:31,419
Shouldn't we tell Jing

243
00:12:31,419 --> 00:12:32,440
about something

244
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:33,179
this serious?

245
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:34,840
I just don't know

246
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,240
if she can break away from work now.

247
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:37,000
I'll take care of it.

248
00:12:38,220 --> 00:12:39,220
You have had a long day.

249
00:12:39,580 --> 00:12:40,539
Go home and get some rest.

250
00:12:41,039 --> 00:12:41,740
It's fine.

251
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:45,960
Let's head out then.

252
00:12:47,259 --> 00:12:47,919
We'll go now.

253
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:49,899
By the way,

254
00:12:50,779 --> 00:12:51,519
please don't

255
00:12:51,639 --> 00:12:52,120
mention this

256
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,019
at the company.

257
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,059
Just pretend you don't know.

258
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:55,480
Okay

259
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:56,679
Bye.

260
00:12:57,259 --> 00:12:57,600
Let's go.

261
00:13:19,299 --> 00:13:20,419
The patient will wake up from

262
00:13:20,419 --> 00:13:21,659
anesthesia in about half an hour.

263
00:13:22,399 --> 00:13:23,919
Given the severity of her condition,

264
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,980
please stay with her at all times.

265
00:13:26,399 --> 00:13:27,139
Do not leave her unattended.

266
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:43,960
What's Jing gonna do?

267
00:13:44,379 --> 00:13:46,019
She's still away on a business trip,

268
00:13:46,220 --> 00:13:47,139
and now her mom...

269
00:13:48,980 --> 00:13:49,720
Who could've

270
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,019
seen this coming?

271
00:13:51,340 --> 00:13:52,220
Good thing she's got a brother,

272
00:13:53,019 --> 00:13:54,500
though they're not blood-related.

273
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,080
But...

274
00:13:57,159 --> 00:13:57,919
Yu,

275
00:13:58,220 --> 00:13:59,799
is Ms. Wei

276
00:13:59,799 --> 00:14:01,700
his stepmother?

277
00:14:02,580 --> 00:14:03,240
I don't know.

278
00:14:04,039 --> 00:14:05,379
Jing rarely talks

279
00:14:05,379 --> 00:14:06,320
about her family.

280
00:14:07,059 --> 00:14:08,240
But she did tell me

281
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:08,980
that she came to Vineton

282
00:14:08,980 --> 00:14:10,480
with her mom when she was little.

283
00:14:11,179 --> 00:14:12,879
If Chen Yi really is her brother,

284
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:14,539
then it's probably true.

285
00:14:14,759 --> 00:14:17,120
No wonder Chen told me

286
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,080
not to talk about it.

287
00:14:18,379 --> 00:14:19,980
He's really considerate.

288
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,559
For someone who isn't related by blood,

289
00:14:24,559 --> 00:14:25,700
he's gone far for her.

290
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:30,919
- Let's take a taxi home.
- Yeah, sure.

291
00:14:30,919 --> 00:14:31,559
Let's go.

292
00:14:57,179 --> 00:14:58,139
Jing is away on a business trip.

293
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:03,980
Don't talk yet.

294
00:15:05,620 --> 00:15:06,500
I need to ask you something.

295
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:08,580
Just nod if I'm right.

296
00:15:12,340 --> 00:15:13,600
You came back this time

297
00:15:16,100 --> 00:15:16,820
to ask Jing for money?

298
00:15:23,899 --> 00:15:24,340
If you don't want money,

299
00:15:25,799 --> 00:15:27,259
are you expecting her to take care of you?

300
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:56,159
I called her.

301
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,100
She'll be back tonight.

302
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:04,840
I don't need your help.

303
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,220
Don't worry.

304
00:16:08,940 --> 00:16:09,700
I'm not doing this for you.

305
00:16:31,179 --> 00:16:31,899
How is she?

306
00:16:35,399 --> 00:16:36,919
The doctor said it's her breast.

307
00:16:37,399 --> 00:16:38,220
I'll go ask for

308
00:16:39,179 --> 00:16:40,159
more details with you.

309
00:16:42,159 --> 00:16:42,620
Let's go.

310
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:58,659
You can go home first.

311
00:16:58,960 --> 00:16:59,940
I'll stay here tonight.

312
00:17:01,559 --> 00:17:02,399
I'll stay with you.

313
00:17:03,379 --> 00:17:05,019
And I'll find a caregiver tomorrow,

314
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:06,740
so you can get some rest.

315
00:17:14,380 --> 00:17:15,059
Don't worry.

316
00:17:15,940 --> 00:17:16,519
I'm here.

317
00:18:59,859 --> 00:19:00,920
I'm fine.

318
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:05,460
I'll be discharged in a few days.

319
00:19:09,460 --> 00:19:10,940
I'll find you a caregiver tomorrow.

320
00:19:11,559 --> 00:19:12,259
I have to work and won't

321
00:19:12,259 --> 00:19:13,039
have time to come by during the day.

322
00:19:13,039 --> 00:19:13,579
No need.

323
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:18,799
Either you listen to me,

324
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:21,240
or you're on your own.

325
00:19:46,079 --> 00:19:46,680
[Hello, Yi.]

326
00:19:47,579 --> 00:19:48,779
[You asked me to have Gordo]

327
00:19:48,779 --> 00:19:49,640
[look into Wei Mingzhen before.]

328
00:19:50,099 --> 00:19:51,500
[They just got back to me.]

329
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:52,980
[They found out]

330
00:19:52,980 --> 00:19:54,519
[she remarried in Rocford.]

331
00:19:54,839 --> 00:19:55,680
[Her new husband had a son,]

332
00:19:56,420 --> 00:19:57,500
[and his family seemed]

333
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,180
[pretty well-off.]

334
00:20:03,359 --> 00:20:03,799
Come in.

335
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:08,480
Hello,

336
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:09,859
I'm Wei Mingzhen's family.

337
00:20:09,859 --> 00:20:10,779
She's in Bed 18.

338
00:20:11,579 --> 00:20:12,339
What's your relation with her?

339
00:20:13,099 --> 00:20:13,599
I'm her daughter.

340
00:20:14,519 --> 00:20:15,339
Sounds like

341
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:16,680
she's been doing alright these years.

342
00:20:17,420 --> 00:20:18,700
So why did she come back?

343
00:20:20,579 --> 00:20:21,960
[Not necessarily.]

344
00:20:22,559 --> 00:20:23,380
[The guy]

345
00:20:23,380 --> 00:20:24,259
[has a son,]

346
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:26,220
who should be in middle school now.

347
00:20:26,740 --> 00:20:27,720
My friend in Rocford

348
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:28,619
sells insurance.

349
00:20:29,019 --> 00:20:29,559
[He found]

350
00:20:29,559 --> 00:20:30,460
[an inquiry record]

351
00:20:30,460 --> 00:20:31,140
[from Wei Mingzhen]

352
00:20:31,420 --> 00:20:32,960
[for a cancer insurance plan.]

353
00:20:33,660 --> 00:20:34,940
[But it was pretty expensive,]

354
00:20:35,180 --> 00:20:36,000
[and nothing came of it.]

355
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:37,700
Late-stage cancer?

356
00:20:38,619 --> 00:20:39,880
I thought she only needed a few days

357
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:40,640
of observation.

358
00:20:41,099 --> 00:20:42,039
Let me walk you through

359
00:20:42,039 --> 00:20:42,940
her condition first.

360
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:46,480
She is currently at

361
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:47,839
Stage IV breast cancer.

362
00:20:48,299 --> 00:20:49,180
That means it's terminal.

363
00:20:50,299 --> 00:20:52,779
The cancer has already spread to her bones,

364
00:20:52,779 --> 00:20:55,960
skull, liver, lungs,

365
00:20:56,140 --> 00:20:58,339
pleura, and other areas.

366
00:20:58,819 --> 00:20:59,599
In other words,

367
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:00,559
it has metastasized.

368
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:02,339
Her vital organs

369
00:21:02,339 --> 00:21:03,079
are also

370
00:21:03,180 --> 00:21:05,279
beginning to fail.

371
00:21:06,619 --> 00:21:07,880
At this stage,

372
00:21:08,119 --> 00:21:09,200
treatment focuses on

373
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,480
relieving her pain

374
00:21:10,859 --> 00:21:12,559
and extending her life.

375
00:21:14,559 --> 00:21:16,180
This is her pathology report.

376
00:21:16,380 --> 00:21:17,160
You can take a look.

377
00:21:21,380 --> 00:21:22,180
The results show

378
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:23,180
that she had received

379
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:24,960
medication treatment before,

380
00:21:25,339 --> 00:21:27,079
but it appears she

381
00:21:27,079 --> 00:21:28,000
hasn't continued treatment

382
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:28,759
for the past year.

383
00:21:29,059 --> 00:21:29,619
That's why

384
00:21:29,619 --> 00:21:30,980
the cancer spread so rapidly

385
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:32,619
and her condition deteriorated so quickly.

386
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:36,559
[I heard she was hospitalized]

387
00:21:36,559 --> 00:21:37,720
[for quite a while.]

388
00:21:38,099 --> 00:21:39,059
[The guy couldn't afford to support]

389
00:21:39,059 --> 00:21:40,259
[both a sick wife and a kid,]

390
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:41,380
[so they split up.]

391
00:21:42,660 --> 00:21:43,579
Okay. I got it.

392
00:21:44,099 --> 00:21:44,880
Get some sleep.

393
00:21:56,579 --> 00:21:57,920
This afternoon her condition was critical.

394
00:21:58,680 --> 00:21:59,200
With

395
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,160
no immediate family

396
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:01,000
present,

397
00:22:01,539 --> 00:22:02,140
we performed

398
00:22:02,140 --> 00:22:03,680
emergency treatment

399
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:04,559
according to protocol.

400
00:22:05,339 --> 00:22:07,259
You have no objection, correct?

401
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:09,299
Alright.

402
00:22:11,579 --> 00:22:13,319
These are the informed consent form

403
00:22:13,319 --> 00:22:14,259
and surgical consent form.

404
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:16,039
You need to sign them.

405
00:22:30,619 --> 00:22:33,039
How much time does she have left?

406
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:36,839
It's not looking good.

407
00:22:37,839 --> 00:22:39,259
Given her current condition,

408
00:22:40,420 --> 00:22:41,400
at most one month.

409
00:22:44,359 --> 00:22:45,339
Is there anything we can do?

410
00:22:46,059 --> 00:22:46,799
There are

411
00:22:47,339 --> 00:22:47,900
two options.

412
00:22:49,059 --> 00:22:50,559
One is chemotherapy alone.

413
00:22:51,599 --> 00:22:52,579
The other is

414
00:22:52,579 --> 00:22:53,720
chemotherapy

415
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:54,839
with targeted drugs.

416
00:22:55,460 --> 00:22:56,180
But

417
00:22:57,079 --> 00:22:58,059
that treatment would be

418
00:22:58,059 --> 00:22:59,079
very costly.

419
00:23:00,220 --> 00:23:01,160
Honestly,

420
00:23:01,319 --> 00:23:03,079
considering her current condition,

421
00:23:03,420 --> 00:23:04,440
the outcomes of both options

422
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:05,240
may not be very different.

423
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:08,259
Either way,

424
00:23:08,259 --> 00:23:09,839
be prepared for what's ahead.

425
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:11,299
Think it over,

426
00:23:11,299 --> 00:23:12,279
and let me know which

427
00:23:13,039 --> 00:23:13,980
treatment plan you choose,

428
00:23:14,279 --> 00:23:14,720
okay?

429
00:24:11,079 --> 00:24:11,819
One yuan.

430
00:24:52,099 --> 00:24:52,900
Don't start smoking.

431
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:54,200
It's bad for your lungs.

432
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:02,900
I brought the blanket up,

433
00:25:03,180 --> 00:25:03,839
and she's asleep now.

434
00:25:04,799 --> 00:25:06,779
Tomorrow, I'll move her to a private room

435
00:25:07,539 --> 00:25:08,400
and go home to grab

436
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:09,099
some clean clothes for her.

437
00:25:15,380 --> 00:25:16,880
I'll go back to hand over my work

438
00:25:17,099 --> 00:25:18,000
and take a few days off.

439
00:25:19,460 --> 00:25:20,380
I've decided.

440
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:22,279
I'm gonna get her treated.

441
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:55,079
Alright, alright.

442
00:25:57,380 --> 00:25:58,019
I'm not tired.

443
00:25:58,019 --> 00:25:58,940
Don't worry.

444
00:26:00,299 --> 00:26:01,539
Is my baby home from school?

445
00:26:03,180 --> 00:26:04,240
Let me talk to her.

446
00:26:06,559 --> 00:26:07,859
Sweetheart,

447
00:26:08,460 --> 00:26:10,240
have you missed Grandma?

448
00:26:12,319 --> 00:26:14,819
I've missed you so much.

449
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:18,500
Did your teacher praise you today?

450
00:26:19,619 --> 00:26:21,119
Good girl.

451
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:22,420
I will

452
00:26:22,420 --> 00:26:23,240
bring you

453
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:25,119
a pink barbie doll later.

454
00:26:26,759 --> 00:26:27,940
Okay, okay.

455
00:26:28,599 --> 00:26:29,599
Bye.

456
00:26:30,099 --> 00:26:30,960
See you soon.

457
00:26:36,220 --> 00:26:36,799
No.

458
00:26:36,799 --> 00:26:37,420
Wait.

459
00:26:37,859 --> 00:26:38,660
Just call me

460
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:39,920
if you need anything.

461
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:41,440
I'll get it for you.

462
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:42,420
You need some water?

463
00:26:43,259 --> 00:26:44,000
Here. Take a sip.

464
00:26:45,059 --> 00:26:46,000
Drink slowly.

465
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:57,799
Careful.

466
00:27:01,140 --> 00:27:03,099
You're this sick

467
00:27:03,380 --> 00:27:03,900
and your daughter

468
00:27:03,900 --> 00:27:05,099
hasn't even come to see you?

469
00:27:07,460 --> 00:27:09,119
She's at work.

470
00:27:12,319 --> 00:27:13,619
They really need her there.

471
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:16,700
No matter how busy she is,

472
00:27:16,839 --> 00:27:17,440
she should

473
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:19,019
look after you when you're sick.

474
00:27:19,900 --> 00:27:21,799
What good is it if she doesn't care?

475
00:27:22,079 --> 00:27:23,240
She'll be here soon.

476
00:27:27,299 --> 00:27:28,880
Besides, I'm fine.

477
00:27:35,259 --> 00:27:36,839
She's so busy with work.

478
00:27:37,039 --> 00:27:38,039
Is she dating anyone?

479
00:27:40,779 --> 00:27:41,859
You may

480
00:27:42,579 --> 00:27:43,980
not be worried now,

481
00:27:43,980 --> 00:27:44,740
but when you

482
00:27:45,279 --> 00:27:47,400
see others become

483
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:48,460
grandparents,

484
00:27:48,900 --> 00:27:49,960
you'll start worrying.

485
00:27:53,279 --> 00:27:54,099
So noisy.

486
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:58,000
You mean the TV is too loud?

487
00:27:58,579 --> 00:27:59,420
I'll turn it off.

488
00:28:11,180 --> 00:28:12,000
Have some more.

489
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:12,839
Come on.

490
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:17,220
Here.

491
00:28:19,099 --> 00:28:21,180
Good. You need to eat more.

492
00:28:24,119 --> 00:28:24,720
Mei,

493
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:26,079
you can go home.

494
00:28:26,420 --> 00:28:27,160
I'll stay with her.

495
00:28:31,019 --> 00:28:31,859
She didn't eat much.

496
00:28:31,859 --> 00:28:32,740
Try to get her to eat a little more.

497
00:28:36,940 --> 00:28:37,420
Call me

498
00:28:37,420 --> 00:28:38,299
if you need anything.

499
00:28:38,700 --> 00:28:39,180
Okay.

500
00:28:54,940 --> 00:28:56,240
What are you doing here?

501
00:28:58,980 --> 00:29:00,559
I took some time off.

502
00:29:00,819 --> 00:29:02,440
I'll stay with you for a couple of days.

503
00:29:04,579 --> 00:29:05,819
Why did you take time off?

504
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,500
Go back to work.

505
00:29:08,140 --> 00:29:09,119
Making money matters more.

506
00:29:12,660 --> 00:29:14,200
In your eyes,

507
00:29:14,759 --> 00:29:16,220
money will always come first.

508
00:29:16,940 --> 00:29:18,319
A woman has nothing

509
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:21,059
if she doesn't have money.

510
00:30:20,019 --> 00:30:20,660
What's wrong?

511
00:30:25,279 --> 00:30:25,799
Does it hurt?

512
00:30:32,940 --> 00:30:33,660
Move up a bit.

513
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:45,039
Here.

514
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:52,480
Easy, easy.

515
00:31:02,799 --> 00:31:04,019
Lying all day feels awful.

516
00:31:07,599 --> 00:31:09,519
I wanna go down and take a walk.

517
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:12,900
Dr. Cui said you can't walk around yet.

518
00:31:38,259 --> 00:31:39,299
The doctor said

519
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:40,019
you can still

520
00:31:40,019 --> 00:31:41,599
go outside in a wheelchair for some air.

521
00:32:27,099 --> 00:32:27,799
Mom!

522
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:30,079
Doctor, please save her!

523
00:32:30,400 --> 00:32:32,920
Mom, please hold on!

524
00:32:33,740 --> 00:32:35,059
Don't leave me!

525
00:32:39,759 --> 00:32:40,700
Looks like

526
00:32:42,039 --> 00:32:44,019
they're fighting death.

527
00:32:46,119 --> 00:32:47,039
After I die,

528
00:32:48,099 --> 00:32:49,440
will you burn joss paper for me?

529
00:32:53,140 --> 00:32:54,259
How much do you want?

530
00:32:54,259 --> 00:32:55,259
The more, the better.

531
00:32:57,259 --> 00:32:58,460
With it,

532
00:32:59,940 --> 00:33:01,400
many things can be taken care of.

533
00:33:20,980 --> 00:33:22,619
Take this money

534
00:33:23,319 --> 00:33:24,839
and buy joss paper for me.

535
00:33:26,559 --> 00:33:27,640
No need to burn a lot every year.

536
00:33:29,180 --> 00:33:30,680
Just don't forget.

537
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:37,099
Let's go back and sleep.

538
00:35:13,199 --> 00:35:13,719
Miao Jing.

539
00:35:14,039 --> 00:35:14,840
She's missing.

540
00:35:20,980 --> 00:35:22,440
Stay calm. I'll have the nurse check the cameras.

541
00:35:22,840 --> 00:35:23,599
Let's go look for her.

542
00:35:31,659 --> 00:35:32,139
Excuse me,

543
00:35:32,519 --> 00:35:33,340
have you seen the patient

544
00:35:33,340 --> 00:35:33,980
from Bed 18?

545
00:35:34,139 --> 00:35:34,679
No.

546
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:35,619
Okay. Thanks.

547
00:36:26,500 --> 00:36:27,300
Come on. Let's go back.

548
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:43,179
I don't wanna be

549
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:47,579
some pathetic, failed,

550
00:36:49,659 --> 00:36:51,099
and haggard woman.

551
00:36:55,900 --> 00:36:57,500
Even if it's my last moment,

552
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:03,519
I wanna

553
00:37:07,420 --> 00:37:08,599
look beautiful.

554
00:37:09,940 --> 00:37:11,199
Don't say such foolish things.

555
00:37:12,659 --> 00:37:14,239
Even if I have to die,

556
00:37:22,099 --> 00:37:23,079
I don't wanna die

557
00:37:23,079 --> 00:37:24,179
in that tiny bed,

558
00:37:28,159 --> 00:37:29,719
looking miserable and helpless,

559
00:37:31,780 --> 00:37:33,280
like an old rag.

560
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:47,480
What's wrong?

561
00:37:53,820 --> 00:37:54,480
Jing,

562
00:37:59,260 --> 00:38:00,599
I promise you

563
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:03,880
I'll be

564
00:38:08,059 --> 00:38:09,219
a better mom

565
00:38:11,119 --> 00:38:12,480
from now on.

566
00:39:10,619 --> 00:39:11,760
You lazy bum!

567
00:39:14,280 --> 00:39:15,000
Gosh,

568
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:15,980
hurry up!

569
00:39:16,199 --> 00:39:17,400
Cooking takes forever.

570
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:18,500
I'm starving.

571
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:20,420
Are you trying to kill me,

572
00:39:21,099 --> 00:39:21,820
lazy bum?

573
00:39:22,300 --> 00:39:22,920
What did you say?

574
00:39:23,679 --> 00:39:24,320
Get out.

575
00:39:25,039 --> 00:39:25,980
Get over here.

576
00:39:26,239 --> 00:39:26,960
Come here.

577
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:27,800
That's how you talk to your cousin?

578
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:29,480
Watch your mouth.

579
00:39:30,519 --> 00:39:31,360
What are you doing?

580
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:31,840
What am I doing?

581
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:32,260
Why are you hitting my son?

582
00:39:32,260 --> 00:39:33,119
Didn't you hear how he was talking?

583
00:39:33,119 --> 00:39:33,559
Get lost.

584
00:39:33,559 --> 00:39:34,260
Go inside and do your homework.

585
00:39:34,260 --> 00:39:34,719
Move,

586
00:39:35,460 --> 00:39:36,219
you brat.

587
00:39:36,219 --> 00:39:37,579
How is the meal still not ready?

588
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:38,920
It's been ages.

589
00:39:40,940 --> 00:39:41,980
You're useless

590
00:39:41,980 --> 00:39:42,960
at everything.

591
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:49,659
Mingzhen,

592
00:39:49,659 --> 00:39:50,659
- Sis.
- what brings you here?

593
00:39:51,079 --> 00:39:52,380
I came back to see you.

594
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:53,679
Where is Jing?

595
00:39:53,679 --> 00:39:54,119
She's

596
00:39:54,119 --> 00:39:54,780
inside.

597
00:39:55,719 --> 00:39:56,760
Has Jing been good?

598
00:39:57,420 --> 00:39:58,300
She's a good girl.

599
00:39:58,300 --> 00:39:59,500
Don't worry. She's doing just fine.

600
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:01,579
Actually, I came back

601
00:40:01,579 --> 00:40:04,440
this time to take Jing home.

602
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:05,360
She's been staying

603
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:06,320
with you for so long,

604
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:07,300
and I hate to keep bothering you.

605
00:40:07,300 --> 00:40:07,860
Alright.

606
00:40:09,159 --> 00:40:09,440
Oh,

607
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:10,019
these are

608
00:40:10,019 --> 00:40:11,539
for you and your husband.

609
00:40:12,340 --> 00:40:13,059
You really didn't have to

610
00:40:13,340 --> 00:40:14,019
bring anything.

611
00:40:14,019 --> 00:40:15,119
Let me get you some water.

612
00:40:32,340 --> 00:40:33,099
Jing,

613
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,440
I'm here to pick you up.

614
00:40:36,719 --> 00:40:37,739
I'm taking you home.

615
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:51,320
Of course.

616
00:40:51,320 --> 00:40:51,980
We're

617
00:40:51,980 --> 00:40:54,099
gonna be together every day.

618
00:40:54,539 --> 00:40:55,260
I'll take you

619
00:40:55,260 --> 00:40:57,019
to the amusement park.

620
00:40:57,019 --> 00:40:58,539
We'll ride the roller coaster,

621
00:40:58,539 --> 00:40:59,440
set off fireworks,

622
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:00,639
and eat hamburgers. Sound good?

623
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:01,199
Okay.

624
00:41:01,460 --> 00:41:02,599
Whatever you want to do,

625
00:41:02,599 --> 00:41:03,679
we'll do it together.

626
00:41:04,219 --> 00:41:05,260
Anything other kids have,

627
00:41:05,739 --> 00:41:07,380
you'll have too.

628
00:41:13,260 --> 00:41:13,679
Here.

629
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:02,760
The morgue charges by the day.

630
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:04,639
Please arrange the funeral soon.

631
00:42:22,360 --> 00:42:23,460
One of you, come handle the paperwork.

632
00:42:43,579 --> 00:42:44,519
I'll go handle it.

633
00:42:46,900 --> 00:42:47,599
Wait here for me.

634
00:43:07,719 --> 00:43:08,500
I'll be back soon.
